<TITLE> Hasina, Khaleda hail fantastic Tigers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 21 (bdnews24.com)  Both the Prime minister Sheikh Hasina and BNP chairperson and Leader of the Opposition Khaleda Zia led the tributes on Tuesday following Bangladesh's historic away Test series triumph. The two leaders hailed the cricketers, captain, coaches, and team management as well as the Bangladesh Cricket Board officials on their first-ever away Test series triumph against the West Indies in Grenada. Bangladesh sealed the two-match series after inflicting a four-wicket defeat on the hosts with a day to spare. They had earlier won the first Test by 95 runs in St Vincent. Mentioning the national cricket team's successes during the tenure of the Awami League-lead government, the Prime minister said whenever Awami League rules the nation; the country achieves success in sports in international arena and this Test series is also the continuation of that. She also urged the national team to maintain the habit of winning in future. Khaleda Zia hoped that the national cricket team would maintain the performance what they put up against West Indies in the two Tests series. Speaker of the Jatiya Sangsad Abdul Hamid praised the performance of the national team and greeted all players, officials and well-wishers of the team. Hamid said that this victory would play a vital role in taking Bangladesh cricket to forward. Chief whip Syeda Sajeda Chowdhury said that the triumph made the whole nation proud. Praising the performance of the national team, state minister for youth and sports Ahad Ali Sarker said the 14-crore people of the country prayed for the national cricket team and that's why it was possible to record an historic series win. The parliamentary standing committee on the youth and sports ministry, the Bangladesh Football Federation, the Bangladesh Olympic Association, national team sponsor Grameenphone and the Cricketers' Welfare Association of Bangladesh also congratulated the national tea
